info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued October 25 at 8:41PM CDT until October 28 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...Forecast flooding changed from Minor to Moderate severity and increased in duration for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Yellow River at Babcock affecting Wood County. For the Yellow River...including Babcock...Moderate flooding is forecast. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL SATURDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Yellow River at Babcock. * WHEN...Until Saturday evening. * IMPACTS...At 15.6 feet, Floodwaters are near a couple of homes in the Babcock area near Highway 173. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:00 PM CDT Wednesday the stage was 14.5 feet. - Bankfull stage is 10.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 8:00 PM CDT Wednesday was 14.5 feet. - Forecast...The river will rise to 15.9 feet tomorrow morning. It will then fall below flood stage by late tomorrow afternoon and then to 9.3 feet Friday morning. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Thursday afternoon.
